    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2019-07-30</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2021-11-23T18:31:27Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>This bill establishes a point of order against legislation that increases long-term direct spending. The point of order may be raised in the House or the Senate against legislation that would cause a net increase in direct spending of more than $5 billion in any of the four consecutive 10-fiscal year periods beginning with the first fiscal year that is 10 fiscal years after the current fiscal year. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To amend the Congressional Budget and Impoundment Control Act of 1974 to establish a point of order against long-term direct spending, and for other purposes.</title>
